title: Policy3265(V)(s2)
type: text/vnd.tiddlywiki

Donated Capital Assets must be reported at fair market value plus ancillary charges, if any, at the time of donation. Donated assets are depreciated over their useful lives as determined for each asset class. If determining historical costs is not practical due to inadequate records, reporting should be based on estimates of fair market value at the date of donation.
